<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14099">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/First%20Aid.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13324">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Handling a First Aid Emergency.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13331">
        (a) Explain the steps necessary to assess and handle a first aid
        emergency, including a safety evaluation of the scene. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.redcross.org/take-a-class/resources/articles/the-three-cs-of-first-aid-check-call-care"
          target="_blank"
          >The 3 C's of First Aid: Check, Call, Care (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/nrNAhMg-uS4?si=ylunwA5D8hAqAOcu"
          target="_blank"
          >Check for Scene Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13332">
        (b) Tell how you would obtain emergency medical assistance from your
        home and from a remote location on a wilderness camping trip. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/spGJ9Ii5W3o" target="_blank"
          >What to Say When You Call 911 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/J3efgWPPp4k" target="_blank"
          >What Happens When You Call 911 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.medstarhealth.org/blog/preparing-for-medical-emergencies-at-home"
          target="_blank"
          >Preparing for a Medical Emergency at Home (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://ncoae.org/blog/when-to-call-or-not-call-for-help-during-a-wilderness-emergency/"
          target="_blank"
          >Calling for Help for a Wilderness Emergency (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13333">
        (c) Demonstrate the precautions you must take to reduce the risk of
        transmitting an infection between you and the victim while administering
        first aid, including the safe disposal of used first aid supplies.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rdKWvw8CZLg" target="_blank"
          >Standard Precautions (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kesQF_G3pQ8?si=89uHvaZRRuoy3mBu"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Remove Disposable Gloves (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tpovFysp4IE" target="_blank"
          >Using Personal Protective Equipment in First Aid (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13334">
        (d) Demonstrate evaluation of and management of a patient's airway and
        breathing. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/7NNe_Qje3yg?si=2hoWHZGQutU5Q2GD"
          target="_blank"
          >Head Tilt, Chin Lift, Jaw Thrust (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hk1_Bcp3Gc0?si=V1kVr9paHb3O8jDJ"
          target="_blank"
          >Look, Listen, Feel (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13335">
        (e) Demonstrate a thorough examination of an accident victim. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/7xANZ0IjgEs?si=qAupHu1rGfl0bqas"
          target="_blank"
          >Head to Toe Exam (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13336">
        (f) Discuss why shock is an emergency. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4-cPuXaZACg" target="_blank"
          >Recognizing Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/He1RQ9STCHc" target="_blank"
          >Shock From Bleeding (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/V4R9GSah93g" target="_blank"
          >Shock and Bleeding (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13324 mb-requirement-id-13337">
        (g) Define the term triage and describe examples of triage situations
        that you may encounter. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_IdJD7UDN2w" target="_blank"
          >Multiple Casualties in a Remote Location (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/zeC2hFcziZI?si=YRyMCxm9qKxLbiZv"
          target="_blank"
          >Triage (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13273">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Preparing for First Aid Emergencies.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13273 mb-requirement-id-13274">
        (a) Obtain a copy of the Scout Annual Health and Medical Record and
        discuss the importance of the form including information on
        immunizations, allergies, medications, health history, and medical
        examinations to providing first aid at Scouting events. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/annual-health-and-medical-record/"
          target="_blank"
          >Scout Health Forms (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13273 mb-requirement-id-13275">
        (b) Using checklists provided in the <em>First Aid</em> merit badge
        pamphlet or ones approved by your counselor, do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13275 mb-requirement-id-13338">
        (1) Assemble a personal first-aid kit for hiking and backpacking.
        Demonstrate the proper use of each item in your first-aid kit to your
        counselor.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/First%20Aid/Personal%20Family%20Troop%20First%20Aid%20Kit%20Checklist.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Personal, Family, and Troop First Aid Kit Checklist (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://scoutlife.org/video-audio/4937/first-aid-kit-buying-guide/"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid KIt Checklists (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13275 mb-requirement-id-13339">
        (2) With your counselor, inspect a unit, home, vehicle, or camp
        first-aid kit and discuss your findings.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13328">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Wounds with No External Bleeding.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs
      of, show first aid for, and explain prevention of these wounds: <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/OxPlCkTKhzY" target="_blank"
        >The Science of Skin (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TLVwELDMDWs" target="_blank"
        >How a Wound Heals Itself (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7qgyBZFaIds?si=cQfOGccpFn-nXeYR" target="_blank"
        >How Wounds Heal (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13340">
        (a) Closed wounds, such as a bruise (contusion) or a hematoma <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DkOmr3BEkvE" target="_blank"
          >Bruise: What to Do (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/first-aid/first-aid-bruise/basics/art-20056663"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Bruises (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bc28m7Ryumg" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for a Hematoma (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/l-HUjlBMuNU" target="_blank"
          >How Bruises Change Color (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13341">
        (b) Superficial, partial thickness, and full thickness thermal (heat)
        burns or scalds <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_kkPXV3l4-M" target="_blank"
          >Types of Burns (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xTu2WdTJgPA" target="_blank"
          >Thermal, Chemical and Electrical Burns (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13342">
        (c) Chemical burns <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/22350-chemical-burns"
          target="_blank"
          >Chemical Burns (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13343">
        (d) Electrical burns <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/first-aid/first-aid-electrical-burns/basics/art-20056687"
          target="_blank"
          >Electrical Burns (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13344">
        (e) Sunburn <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DCNUwuNTtGg" target="_blank"
          >Sunburn (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/-KzTvagnpfU?si=WsU5V3PV1KLY8xSo"
          target="_blank"
          >Sunburn, Causes, Signs and Symptoms, Diagnosis and Treatment
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13345">
        (f) Snow blindness <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6MRQBMFlFTU" target="_blank"
          >Snow Blindness (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13346">
        (g) Immersion foot, frostnip, frostbite, and ice burns <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/b8Th0JIDBW4?si=IM7GWkbOAiKPVESh"
          target="_blank"
          >Immersion (Trench) Foot (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/24392-trench-foot"
          target="_blank"
          >Immersion (Trench) Foot (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/tPEj-0sKZyo?si=yXzecc6nE9GArjg8"
          target="_blank"
          >Frostbite (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/frostbite/symptoms-causes/syc-20372656"
          target="_blank"
          >Frostbite (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13347">
        (h) Abrasions, such as chafing and rope burns <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://hilltoppacks.com/pages/how-do-i-prevent-chafing-while-hiking"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Prevent Chafing While Hiking (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/rope-burn" target="_blank"
          >Treatment of Rope Burns (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13348">
        (i) Blisters on the hands, feet, buttocks, and shoulders <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.aad.org/public/everyday-care/injured-skin/burns/prevent-treat-blisters"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Prevent and Treat Blisters (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13349">
        (j) Puncture wounds from splinters, rope splinters, nails, and fish
        hooks <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/L6crQ3nMLkI?si=xCGK0gMdSkprXr0s&amp;t=20"
          target="_blank"
          >Splinters (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.homedepot.com/c/ah/how-to-get-a-splinter-out/9ba683603be9fa5395fab9013594e8c7"
          target="_blank"
          >Tips for Removing Splinters, Including Tape and White Glue
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.urgentcareforfeet.com/infection-warning-key-signs-to-monitor-after-a-foot-puncture-injury/"
          target="_blank"
          >Puncture Wounds on the Feet (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AmT3T_9Guq0" target="_blank"
          >Removing a Fishhook (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13350">
        (k) Rash from poisonous plants <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P6aBc4OAD0g" target="_blank"
          >Poisonous Plants (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/10655-poison-plants-poison-ivy--poison-oak--poison-sumac"
          target="_blank"
          >Poisonous Plants (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13351">
        (l) Bug bites of chiggers, ticks, mosquitoes, and biting gnats <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/tcbNBdPRxk8?si=CHF4hwiFywBxs8-U"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Chigger Bites (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.aad.org/public/everyday-care/injured-skin/bites/remove-a-tick"
          target="_blank"
          >Removing a Tick and Preventing Tick Bites (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.aad.org/public/everyday-care/injured-skin/bites/prevent-treat-bug-bites"
          target="_blank"
          >Preventing and Treating Mosquito Bites (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/QazaIwbtZHs?si=zNRtO24W_yqUixr7"
          target="_blank"
          >Biting Gnats (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13352">
        (m) Bee stings <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01Po5RTNfhs" target="_blank"
          >How to Treat a Bee Sting (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/H_wj50ox8OY?si=iInuTacBOgFekPmc"
          target="_blank"
          >What if a Bee Stings You? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/I-LqoDOAX8M" target="_blank"
          >Never Pinch a Bee Sting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13353">
        (n) Bites of spiders <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cfh7XOc_hgc" target="_blank"
          >Black Widow vs Brown Recluse Spider Bites (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/16639-spider-bites"
          target="_blank"
          >Spider Bites (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13354">
        (o) Sting of a scorpion <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YFI2VMy6mT0?si=G-ooMuchiOcxEYQt"
          target="_blank"
          >How Scorpion Stings Work (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/scorpion-stings/symptoms-causes/syc-20353859"
          target="_blank"
          >Scorpion Stings (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13355">
        (p) Bite of a pet or wild mammal or human <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RSJzuk226RI" target="_blank"
          >Treatment of Animal and Human Bites (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13328 mb-requirement-id-13356">
        (q) Bite of a venomous snake <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.snakebitefoundation.org/blog/how-to-treat-snakebites-for-first-responders-in-the-united-states"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Snake Bites (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/yyicCyoEpPM?si=66KVn6Myp25BkpZG"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Snake Bites (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.cdc.gov/niosh/outdoor-workers/about/venomous-snakes.html"
