    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13329">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Bleeding Wounds.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs of, show first aid
      for, and explain prevention of these wounds:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13329 mb-requirement-id-13357">
        (a) A nosebleed. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rF8aXjRFu_I" target="_blank"
          >Nosebleed (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13329 mb-requirement-id-13358">
        (b) An open wound with mild or moderate bleeding, such as a scratch or a
        scrape (abrasions), or a shallow cut (laceration). <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/7bTVimEqkKo?si=Qpro1vC8l4Z42Sx5"
          target="_blank"
          >Care of Minor Wounds (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13329 mb-requirement-id-13359">
        (c) An open wound with severe bleeding such as a deep cut on an arm or
        leg. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YJB3fI3T1oo" target="_blank"
          >Using Direct Pressure to Control Life-Threatening Bleeding (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13329 mb-requirement-id-13360">
        (d) Explain when it is appropriate and is not appropriate to use one or
        more tourniquets. List some of the benefits and dangers of using a
        tourniquet. Demonstrate the application of a tourniquet without
        tightening it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/k98ilfQmUWw?si=3e6zkvJz517hfiE5"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Use a Tourniquet (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/mZTgQikH1sQ" target="_blank"
          >Tourniquet Mistakes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13276">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Breathing Emergencies.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs of, show
      first aid for, and explain prevention of these conditions affecting
      breathing:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13276 mb-requirement-id-13277">
        (a) Choking <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8R3RWC-xx1I" target="_blank"
          >Back Blows and Abdominal Thrusts for Choking (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9pTnepZd5as" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for an Unresponsive Choking Adults (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13276 mb-requirement-id-13278">
        (b) Asthmatic attack <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/batzSytA1Y0" target="_blank"
          >What is Asthma? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/VyqzylUADp0" target="_blank"
          >Using Albuterol for an Asthma Attack (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wcKgqYXF2gA" target="_blank"
          >Pursed Lip Breathing for Asthma (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13276 mb-requirement-id-13361">
        (c) Anaphylaxis from an insect bite or sting or from food or product
        allergy <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/veHAMX6vukY?si=jtG07MJUuoWZVQfU"
          target="_blank"
          >Food Allergy with Anaphylaxis (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/K7QyCMNDHAs?si=T0eBEn7GpbW9BjQa"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Inject an EpiPen (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13276 mb-requirement-id-13362">
        (d) Inhalation injuries <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/YJVGTJPQMEw?si=_HQifwBCjA3Lzgh8"
          target="_blank"
          >Airway Burns (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PqiAtelp-Qc?si=Q2Klj56m0pB95pEm"
          target="_blank"
          >Carbon Monoxide Poisoning (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13276 mb-requirement-id-13363">
        (e) Altitude sickness <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/8D9dwH16GLw?si=HDHXNT8t1mw5QijT"
          target="_blank"
          >High Altitude Illness Treatment and Prevention (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13279">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b>Loss of Consciousness.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs of, show
      first aid for, and explain prevention of these conditions causing loss of
      consciousness:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13280">
        (a) Fainting <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7lTWGG2ZvK4" target="_blank"
          >Fainting (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13281">
        (b) Hypoglycemia <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ASqdE2sqHgM" target="_blank"
          >Diabetic Emergencies (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13282">
        (c) Seizure <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nnpttMlAG_w" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for a Seizure (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13364">
        (d) Drug overdose and alcohol poisoning <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8eUUf5ssH_4" target="_blank"
          >Naloxone Treatment of an Opioid Overdose (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/UqY7DZ46prA?si=BB3yLWOqqxd-jhsG"
          target="_blank"
          >Alcohol Poisoning (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13365">
        (e) Underwater hypoxic blackout <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://underwaterhypoxicblackout.org/" target="_blank"
          >Underwater Blackout (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13366">
        (f) Cold water shock and drowning <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RypLau65Wa0?si=c25FnmssnqvQqecU"
          target="_blank"
          >Understanding Cold Water Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/mnfhnyY-Udk?si=hDJw11X7ejwN54WI"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Perform CPR for a Drowning Victim (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13279 mb-requirement-id-13367">
        (g) Lightning strike and electric shock <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oFLAKfjEjcg?si=GCT03PYYxBdE4jNd"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Electrical Shocks and Lightning Strikes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13283">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Heart Attack.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13284">
        (a) Explain what a heart attack is. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/3_PYnWVoUzM?si=FlnFcSGpYJuxGIo5"
          target="_blank"
          >What Happens During a Heart Attack (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/psx-QcxL1A8" target="_blank"
          >Heart Attack vs. Cardiac Arrest (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13285">
        (b) Describe the symptoms and signs of a heart attack and first aid for
        this condition.<br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/jouwrfr7_S0?si=By1f--Oq9UPUcHkd"
          target="_blank"
          >Symptoms &amp; Signs of a Heart Attack in Women &amp; Men (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13286">
        (c) Describe the conditions that must exist before performing CPR on a
        person. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/DByqyhLV1zg?si=RO4saCDlfXZu2TN6"
          target="_blank"
          >Responding to Cardiac Arrest (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13287">
        (d) Demonstrate proper CPR technique using a training device approved by
        your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/A5PnI4I-vd8?si=ERt7HtnwcmqFJmQA"
          target="_blank"
          >Hands-Only CPR (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13288">
        (e) Explain the use of an automated external defibrillator (AED).
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/in8j2Q2z3HE" target="_blank"
          >Using an AED (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13368">
        (f) Demonstrate or simulate the proper use of an AED, using an AED
        training device if available. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://blog.scoutingmagazine.org/2024/06/13/does-your-scout-unit-have-an-aed/"
          target="_blank"
          >AEDs in Scouting (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13283 mb-requirement-id-13369">
        (g) Identify the typical location(s) of one or more AED(s) at public
        facilities in your community, such as, your school, place of worship,
        unit meeting place, sports facilities, and/or camp or by using a smart
        phone app. Discuss the reasons for choosing locations like these.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://cpr.heart.org/en/-/media/CPR-Files/Training-Programs/AED-Implementation/2023-updates/KJ1683-AED-Guide.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Where to Place AEDs (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13289">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Muscle and Bone Injuries.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13289 mb-requirement-id-13290">
        (a) Explain the similarities and differences in a strain, a muscle tear,
        a tendon rupture, a sprain, a dislocation, a simple fracture, and a
        compound fracture. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qi0YYFt5RCY" target="_blank"
          >Understanding Limb Injuries: Strains, Sprains, Dislocations,
          Fractures (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uyxcdJkFvrw" target="_blank"
          >Muscle Strains and Tears (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xulug1uqisM" target="_blank"
          >Dislocations and Types of Fractures (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13289 mb-requirement-id-13291">
        (b) Describe the symptoms and signs of and first aid for a muscle
        strain, a muscle tear, and a tendon rupture. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IM7BIO_kdk8" target="_blank"
          >Muscle Strains and Tears (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13289 mb-requirement-id-13292">
        (c) Describe the symptoms and signs of, and potential complications of,
        a sprain, a fracture, and a dislocation. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sPzXAVNVJr0" target="_blank"
          >Fractures and Dislocations (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13289 mb-requirement-id-13293">
        (d) Demonstrate bandages for these injuries:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13293 mb-requirement-id-13370">
        (1) Arm slings for forearm or upper arm or collarbone fractures <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ybpr7nCelK0?si=2SjPp8f4iMAzfVBv"
          target="_blank"
          >Bandages for Sprained Ankle, Head, Upper Arm, Collarbone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13293 mb-requirement-id-13371">
        (2) Elastic wrap and cravat bandages for ankle sprain <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KRyaemlcJAM?si=_A2ie3PNfdiH1n-0"
          target="_blank"
          >Elastic Wrap for Ankle Sprain (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13293 mb-requirement-id-13372">
        (3) Elastic wrap and cravat bandages for wrist sprain or hand injury.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tdRMJIu2E08" target="_blank"
          >Wrist Wrap (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13289 mb-requirement-id-13373">
        (e) Demonstrate the proper procedures for handling and splinting of
        suspected closed or open fractures or dislocations of the:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13373 mb-requirement-id-13374">
        (1) Finger and toe <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/P-D0njmVMVA" target="_blank"
          >Buddy Taping Toes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13373 mb-requirement-id-13375">
        (2) Forearm or wrist <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jhXWT4UpC-8" target="_blank"
          >Splints for Arms and Legs (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13373 mb-requirement-id-13376">
        (3) Upper leg <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5KJIojnNAPU?si=qfwme0YazWPIMn0c"
          target="_blank"
          >Upper Leg Splint (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13373 mb-requirement-id-13377">
        (4) Lower leg or ankle <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TacM-3A5Ozk" target="_blank"
          >Leg Splints (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13330">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      <b>Head and Spine Injuries.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13330 mb-requirement-id-13378">
        (a) Describe the symptoms and signs of, relationships between, possible
        complications of, and prevention of head, neck, and back injuries.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/x-YYjkokQ6U?si=m2OLxLuy7hoS7Yiq"
          target="_blank"
          >Head, Neck, and Spine Injuries (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9hEjyLabTRE" target="_blank"
          >Assessing a Head Injury (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13330 mb-requirement-id-13379">
        (b) Describe the symptoms and signs of and first aid for a concussion.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xvjK-4NXRsM" target="_blank"
          >What Is a Concussion? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mlWaByoT24s" target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Concussions (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13330 mb-requirement-id-13380">
        (c) Demonstrate first aid for an open head wound with a triangular or
        other bandage. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/FvAWy4mCm7U?si=lQPX3DLPLhYK1r1Q"
          target="_blank"
          >Forehead Cravat Bandage (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13330 mb-requirement-id-13381">
        (d) Demonstrate first aid for someone with a suspected neck or back
        injury. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/D_ZKcO8Ww_c" target="_blank"
          >Head, Neck, and Spine Injuries During Sports (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13325">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      <b>Moving a Patient.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13325 mb-requirement-id-13382">
        (a) Describe the conditions under which an injured person should and
        should not be moved. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.firstaidbristol.co.uk/blog/2024/09/10/when-is-it-okay-to-move-a-casualty/"
          target="_blank"
          >When to Move an Injured Person (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13325 mb-requirement-id-13383">
        (b) If a sick or an injured person must be moved, tell how you would
        decide the best method. Demonstrate these methods. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.cert-la.com/cert-training-education/lifts-carries/"
          target="_blank"
          >Lifts and Carries (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13325 mb-requirement-id-13384">
        (c) By yourself and with a partner, demonstrate how to transport a
        person from a smoke-filled room. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dC8dC8-ZAoU?si=wQlOwOobpXhJD_3_"
          target="_blank"
        >
          Fire and EMS Training | Moving a Victim | Moving a Patient (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13325 mb-requirement-id-13385">
        (d) By yourself and with a partner, demonstrate how to transport a
        person with a sprained ankle for at least 25 yards. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/U0yDJ0udMkg?si=dB8YruPw7vFL8YC4"
          target="_blank"
          >Human Crutch Techniques (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13325 mb-requirement-id-13386">
        (e) With helpers under your supervision, improvise a stretcher and move
        a presumably unconscious person for at least 25 yards. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/EYfgxODBlwY?si=dNtz-3lO0Lronu8G"
          target="_blank"
          >Improvised Stretchers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13294">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      <b>Heat- and Cold-Related Conditions.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs
      of, show first aid for, and explain prevention of these conditions
      associated with exertion and/or heat or cold exposure:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13295">
        (a) Dehydration and over-hydration <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KahsIEbFROI?si=6m37jPgHqsLiRl_2"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Dehydration? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/sD6j5sNo5Zk" target="_blank"
          >Overhydration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13296">
        (b) Heat cramps and muscle pain after exertion <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KOQJB3jlln4?si=F-O0xr3ak9Hk-rbg"
          target="_blank"
          >Heat Cramps, Heat Exhaustion, and Heat Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/6nZOTJ_8guI?si=UgozPCQZg125bGoC"
          target="_blank"
          >Muscle Damage from Over-exercising (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13297">
        (c) Heat exhaustion <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8gn3DEYOPuE" target="_blank"
          >Heat Exhaustion vs Heat Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13298">
        (d) Heat stroke <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PpHM4DfPZQU?si=mb_BftAlZP8amve9"
          target="_blank"
          >Diagnosis and Treatment of Heat Stroke (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13299">
        (e) Chest pains associated with cold exposure <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/xP6Nya7nH_g?si=Lk2KfMloGzl6ZgPk"
          target="_blank"
          >Heart Attacks from Shoveling Snow (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13294 mb-requirement-id-13300">
        (f) Hypothermia <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/my6JB41apTw" target="_blank"
          >Hypothermia (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/winter-activity/"
          target="_blank"
          >C.O.L.D. Guidelines for Staying warm (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://health.mo.gov/living/healthcondiseases/hypothermia/index.php"
          target="_blank"
          >Frostbite and Hypothermia (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aDAqWLpHXXU" target="_blank"
          >Recognize the "Umbles" and Avoid Hypothermia (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13326">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 12. </span>
      <b>Mental Health Conditions.</b> Describe the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13326 mb-requirement-id-13387">
        (a) Reactions associated with at least three stressful situations, such
        as mountain backpacking, rappelling, a ropes course, speaking before an
        audience, making a phone call to an adult, taking a swim test, missing
        home, lighting a match, trying out for a sports team, meeting someone
        for the first time, or other stressful circumstances. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_H5QFfiU0s0" target="_blank"
          >3 Tools for Situational Anxiety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BmX6GXDvlLM" target="_blank"
          >Overcoming Social Anxiety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gTd6Lq1M9Tc" target="_blank"
          >Power of Self-Confidence (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/a_dVK2EEWKE" target="_blank"
          >Getting Ready for Tryouts (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13326 mb-requirement-id-13388">
        (b) The actions that you and others should take to prepare for and
        manage these situations. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/h2zWopNUUJE" target="_blank"
          >Techniques to Manage Stress (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UC6HUrneIWI" target="_blank"
          >Box Breathing | The Breathing Exercise Used By Navy SEALs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QcKbxaGpwf4" target="_blank"
          >Tips for Overcoming Phone Anxiety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wbroM1Di-bI" target="_blank"
          >How To STOP Letting Social Anxiety Control You (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13326 mb-requirement-id-13389">
        (c) The indications that someone might be a danger to themselves or
        others.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13326 mb-requirement-id-13390">
        (d) The actions that you should take if you suspect that someone might
        be a danger to themselves or others.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13301">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 13. </span>
      <b>Miscellaneous Conditions.</b> Describe the symptoms and signs of, show
      first aid for, and explain prevention of the following conditions:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13301 mb-requirement-id-13302">
        (a) Object in the eye <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/uJFZPFsHcCE?si=YgmlNzHWSWm3iWWH"
          target="_blank"
          >5 Ways To Safely Remove Something Stuck In Your Eye (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/46UgImUrAG0" target="_blank"
          >Penetrating and Chemical Eye Injuries (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13301 mb-requirement-id-13303">
        (b) Broken, chipped, loosened, or knocked out tooth <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/eJnKf1jM6xY" target="_blank"
          >Dental Emergencies (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/16916-dental-injuries"
          target="_blank"
          >Dental Injuries (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13301 mb-requirement-id-13304">
        (c) Vomiting and diarrhea associated with food poisoning <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/K5UxbbnSjxc?si=pf6WbrBictHhwad8"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid for Vomiting and Diarrhea (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13301 mb-requirement-id-13305">
        (d) Abdominal pain <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2RxEHcGpwnA" target="_blank"
          >Causes of Abdominal Pain (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/pFCfQwYWxcM?si=r3inhA-IMeSBDkCz"
          target="_blank"
          >Appendicitis (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/8CUEPNcGtWs?si=c7X8WPlAAwQvtPWC"
          target="_blank"
          >What Does Appendix Pain Feel Like? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-13301 mb-requirement-id-13306">
        (e) Stroke <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EsshJLm5CN8" target="_blank"
          >Types of Strokes (video)</a
